# Project Conventions

- Prefer stacked branches for phased work.
- Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks; never amend unless requested.
- Save implementation plans in `docs/` before starting major changes, linked to Linear issue numbers/projects/milestones.
- Favor defensive defaults and graceful degradation for ML services.
- Keep ingestion/webhooks fast; do heavy work async via Celery.

## Testing Expectations
- Backend: `pytest` (use docker-compose test stack when integration tests are needed).
- Frontend: `npm run lint` for UI changes.
- Verify key endpoints when relevant: `/health`, `/incidents`, `/alerts`, `/chat`.
